# Never copy host-resolved dependencies into the image. Under multi-arch buildx
# (node-tools#5/#6) the build context is populated on the amd64 CI runner (e.g.
# `make test` runs `npm ci` before the image build), so a copied node_modules is
# the WRONG architecture on the arm64 image. esbuild is the sharp edge: it ships
# its native binary as a per-arch optional dep (@esbuild/linux-<arch>), so a
# copied amd64 tree makes importmap_generator / bundle_cjs fail on real arm64.
# Dependencies are installed FRESH per target platform in the Dockerfile.
**/node_modules

# Build/dev-only surfaces that never belong in the runtime image.
.git
.github
bench
docs
